# Next.js 16 Conventions

## Framework

- **Required**: Next.js 16 with App Router
- **Default**: Server Components â€” use `'use client'` only when strictly necessary
- Always justify `'use client'` usage; keep Client Components as leaf nodes

## Cache Components model

`cacheComponents: true` is enabled in `next.config.ts`. Rendering is **dynamic by default**.

### Three tiers

| Tier | Mechanism | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| Static | Sync code, prerendered at build | Page shells, nav, headings |
| Cached | `'use cache'` + `cacheLife()` + `cacheTag()` | Data that can be served stale for minutes/hours |
| Dynamic | `<Suspense>` around async RSC reading `cookies()`/`headers()` | Per-request, user-specific data |

### `'use cache'` rules

- Place the directive at the top of the async function body (component or utility)
- Always call `cacheTag()` to enable targeted invalidation
- Always call `cacheLife()` to set an explicit expiry profile (`'minutes'`, `'hours'`, `'days'`, `'max'`)
- Never access `cookies()`, `headers()`, or `searchParams` inside a cached function â€” extract them outside and pass as arguments

### Invalidation

- `updateTag(tag)` â€” immediate, same-request invalidation (use after mutations in Server Actions)
- `revalidateTag(tag)` â€” background revalidation (next request sees fresh data)

### Migrating old patterns

| Old | New |
|---|---|
| `export const revalidate = N` | `'use cache'` + `cacheLife({ revalidate: N })` |
| `unstable_cache()` | `'use cache'` directive |
| `dynamic = 'force-static'` | `'use cache'` + `cacheLife('max')` |
| `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` | Remove â€” dynamic is the default |
| `experimental.ppr` | `cacheComponents: true` in `next.config.ts` |

## Routing and params

- `params` and `searchParams` are Promises in Next.js 16 â€” always `await` them
- Use `generateStaticParams` for known slugs; it works alongside Cache Components

## Middleware / proxy

- Next.js 16 introduces `proxy.ts` for network boundary control (replaces `middleware.ts` for routing use cases)
- Use `proxy.ts` at the root for rewrite/redirect logic when adding one to this project

## Linting

- `next lint` is removed in Next.js 16 â€” use `eslint .` directly
- ESLint config: flat config at `eslint.config.mjs`

## Turbopack

- Turbopack is the default bundler â€” no `--turbopack` flag needed in scripts
- Custom bundler config goes under top-level `turbopack` in `next.config.ts` (not `experimental`)

## React Compiler

- `reactCompiler: true` is set at the top level in `next.config.ts` (stable in Next.js 16)
- The compiler enforces the Rules of Hooks; ESLint `react-compiler/react-compiler` rule is active
